URL-SHOTNER

URL Shortener using Node.js,ejs and MongoDb, with this application, you can input a long URL, and the app generates a shortened version. When users navigate to the shortened URL, it seamlessly redirects them to the original website. It's a handy tool for creating concise and shareable links, simplifying the process of sharing web addresses.

  • Node

Notes Keeper App

I've developed a straightforward notes app for Android, equipped with a reliable database. This simple yet effective application allows users to easily create, edit, and organize their notes. With the added functionality of a database, users can expect a seamless experience in storing and retrieving their information. The app is designed to be user-friendly, making it a practical solution for anyone looking to manage their notes effortlessly on their Android devices.

  • JAVA
  • Android Studio

User Management System

I've built a distinctive User Management System, creating separate versions using the MERN (MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, Node.js) stack and Java. The MERN implementation focuses on a responsive and dynamic user interface, leveraging the power of React for an interactive experience. On the other hand, the Java version emphasizes robust backend functionality, utilizing Java technologies for seamless operations. Both implementations showcase my skills in developing user-centric systems across different technology stacks.

  • React
  • Node
  • Mongodb
  • Express
  • JAVA

WorkShop Management System

I've developed a comprehensive Workshop Management System using JavaScript, HTML, CSS, and PHP. This system efficiently handles various aspects of workshop management, providing a user-friendly interface for seamless navigation. Users can easily manage workshops, track attendance, and organize schedules. The system's intuitive design ensures a smooth user experience, while the PHP backend ensures robust functionality. This project reflects my proficiency in web development and my ability to create practical solutions for effective workshop management.
